On tap. Deep deep beer. So many levels in this glass it's beyond a single review. I would have to spend a weekend deconstructing it and a thesis would follow. Well worth the price is about all I can say. Treat it like a fine scotch.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Thick on the palate, almost syrupy. Feel the booze in your gut quickly. Love the color, it's avg on taste, but the thick mouthfeel was slightly off putting for me. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

22oz. Looks like a nice porter however the taste is average at best. Purely one dimensional. I was expecting more.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A lot going on in this stout. We were drinking Rogue Chocolate Porter when the bartender told us we gotta try this. It took it to another level! I got smoky almost scotch flavors reminiscent of a campfire weekend with good friends. Excellent brew I will have to seek out to find more of!
